    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-10-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="783"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2222/17: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Third Secretary of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-30">October 30,
                            1936—[?] p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 30—8:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>X–266. Decree of Ministry of War, dated October 29, published in <hi
                        rend="italic">Gaceta de Madrid</hi> today, makes liable for military service
                    all male Spaniards 20 to 45 years of age inclusive. I have addressed <hi
                        rend="italic">note verb ale</hi> to Ministry of State requesting that
                    Spanish employees of the Embassy and Consulate be exempted from provisions of
                    this decree.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wendelin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
